            "lang": "en",
            "value": "Internet Explorer in Windows 10 Gold, 1511, 1607, 1703, and Windows Server 2016 allows an attacker to bypass Device Guard User Mode Code Integrity (UMCI) policies due to Internet Explorer failing to validate UMCI policies, aka \"Internet Explorer Security Feature Bypass Vulnerability\"."
          },
          {
            "lang": "es",
            "value": "Internet Explorer en Windows 10 Gold, 1511, 1607, 1703, y Windows Server 2016 permite que un atacante eluda las políticas Device Guard User Mode Code Integrity (UCMI) debido a que Internet Explorer no valida las políticas UMCI. Esto también se conoce como \"Internet Explorer Security Feature Bypass Vulnerability\"."
          }
        ],
